<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">121.893/12–1045</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                State</gloss> to President <persName type="to">Truman</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-11">December 11,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>There is attached the draft of a proposed letter to General Marshall for your
                            signature.<note n="34" xml:id="d554fn34">For draft by Mr. Vincent
                            revised by Mr. Byrnes on December 10, see <ref target="#pg_764">p.
                                764</ref>; for text signed December 15 by President Truman, see <ref target="#pg_770">p. 770</ref>. The enclosure was the revised draft
                            of Mr. Byrnes; this the President signed.</note> General Marshall, it is
                        understood, desires something in the form of a directive from you before his
                        departure and <pb facs="0777" n="767" xml:id="pg_767"/> the attached letter
                        has been prepared in the Department of State with the thought of meeting
                        General Marshall’s desire.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> F. <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>